    "content": "nullExperience Cloud\nTABLE OF CONTENTS\nClose\nClose\nSearch\nSearch\n Experience Cloud\n Understand the Basics\n Plan & Prepare\n Set Up & Configure\n Manage Users and Data Access\n Build & Customize\n Create Use-Case Driven Sites\n Secure Your Site\n Test & Deploy\n Manage & Moderate\n Managers, Moderators, and Admins Working Together\n Experience Cloud Site Moderation Strategies and Tools\n Organize Experience Cloud Sites with Topics\n Customize Recommendations in Experience Cloud Sites\n Gamification\n Recognition Badges\n Recognition Badges Limitations\n Recognition Badges Setup\n Enable WDC Thanks\n Turn On Recognition Badges in Experience Workspaces\n Configure Who Can Create Recognition Badges\n Configure Who Can Assign Recognition Badges\n Use Components to Display Assigned Recognition Badges on Member...\n Create, Edit, and Delete Recognition Badges\n Manage Who Can Assign a Specific Recognition Badge\n Display the Full List of Assigned Recognition Badges on a Member’s...\n Missions\n Assign Recognition Badges to Experience Cloud Site Members\n Delete Assigned Badges\n Use the API to Give Recognition Badges Sample Code\n Reputation Overview\n Share a Link to Your Experience Cloud Site\n Switch Between Your Salesforce Org and Your Experience Cloud Sites\n Use Reporting in Experience Cloud Sites\n Considerations\n\nYou are here:\n\nSALESFORCE HELP\nDOCS\nEXPERIENCE CLOUD\nTurn On Recognition Badges in Experience Workspaces\n\nTurn on Recognition Badges via the Gamification Tile to finish setting up and start giving badges.\n\nREQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS\nAvailable in: Enterprise, Professional, Unlimited, and Developer editions.\n\n\nUSER PERMISSIONS NEEDED\nTo turn on or off Recognition Badges:\t\n\nCreate and Set Up Experiences\n\nAND\n\nModerate Chatter\n\nBefore completing this task, enable WDC’s Thanks feature, configure permission sets for who can create and give badges, and add recognition to user profile layouts.\n\nIn Experience Workspaces, click the Gamification tile.\nIn Settings, turn on Recognition Badges. A Recognition Badges section appears above Settings.\nTo see the available badges and create and manage badges, click Recognition Badges.\nDID THIS ARTICLE SOLVE YOUR ISSUE?\nLet us know so we can improve!\nYes\nNo\n ",
